(181, 139, 4, 'Protect clean water, protect lives', 'protect-clean-water-protect-lives', 'news/2019/12/5e09b7b0334d2.jpg', 'In the spirits of 2017 Month of Youth, in Ben Tre City, Suntory Holdings Limited (Japan), in coordination with Vietnam Central Council of Ho Chi Minh Young...', '<div class=\"noidung TextSize\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">In the spirits of 2017 Month of Youth, in Ben Tre City, Suntory Holdings Limited (Japan), in coordination with Vietnam Central Council of Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization, Ministry of Education and Training, Vietnam National Union of Student, carried out the kick-off ceremony of &nbsp;&ldquo;2017 Mizuiku - I love clean water&rdquo;.</span></span>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\"><img style=\"width: 665px; height: 449px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/1(2).jpg\" alt=\"Lớp học mẫu trong khu&ocirc;n khổ Chương tr&igrave;nh Mizuiku - Em y&ecirc;u nước sạch.\" /></span></span></span><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">Sample class in the framework of the Mizuiku - I love clean water project.</span></span></span></div>\r\n<span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">Participated in the ceremony were Mr. Nguyen Long Hai, Secretary of Central Committee of Ho Chi Minh communist Youth Union, Chairman of Vietnam Central Council of Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization,&nbsp;and more than 200 teachers, persons in charge of kids from Provinces, Cities and around 1,300 students in Ben Tre Province.</span></span></span><br /><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">Program organizers said: In Japanese, \"Mizu\" means water, \"iku\" means education. Mizuiku is a highly meaningful educational communication program focused on educating children about the role of water resources on the earth, thus helping to </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">protect and reserve clean water resources</span></span><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\"> for future generations. Suntory Holdings Limited (Japan) initiated and implemented the \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\" project in Japan since 2004. Since 2015, Vietnam is the first country - other than Japan - chosen by the Suntory Group to implement this program.</span></span></span><br /><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">Mr. Nguyen Long Hai, Secretary of Central Committee of Ho Chi Minh Communist Youth Union, Chairman of Vietnam Central Council of Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization, Head of the Organizing Committee of the \"2017 Mizuiku - I love clean water\" program, emphasized: \"</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Clean water is a rare and precious resource, and scientists have predicted over the next decade more than four billion people would not access to clean water for at least a month each year. However, every day we are still using it wasteful and polluting the water source</span></span><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">. The \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\" </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">program will help the children, teachers spreading to parents in particular and community in general the awareness of protecting clean water, the environment, and our lives</span></span><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">\".</span></span></span><br /><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">At the ceremony, Mr. Naiki Kenji, Senior Head of Communications of Suntory Holdings, said: \"We expect the project will have a positive impact on Vietnamese primary students who will take the key role in environmental protection in the future as the project has been effective in Japan\".</span></span></span><br /><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">In the first lesson at the kick&ndash;off ceremony, students of Ben Tre Primary School, Ben Tre Province had opportunities to be exposed to exhibitions on lively paintings, short animated films, which helped to deliver useful and practical messages on water scarcity all over the world in general and in Vietnam in particular. It is to raise the awareness among children about the importance of clean water resources for a better life as well as how to protect themselves from severe consequences of water pollution.</span></span></span><br /><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">Previously, in 2015-2016, the \"Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water\" project has hosted </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">more than 400 classes for around 5,000 students, 16 Water Festivals for over 7,700 students and the construction of water filtration systems and restrooms for over 16 primary schools participating in the program</span></span><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">; In 2017, the project will involve 30 primary schools in Bac Ninh, Hanoi, Ho Chi Minh City and Ben Tre Province with the key activities such as teaching the students in the third and fourth grade about the environment on water topics under the Mizuiku program, including: water types, water cycle; the role of water in life; today\'s issue of water and the impact of water issues on life; building the habit of saving water, protecting the environment; practicing water filtration test, etc.</span></span></span></div>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 4, '0', '2018-03-21 02:11:00', 33, '2019-12-30 08:40:20', 33, NULL, NULL),
(182, 164, 4, 'Comic series \"Mizu – A Talking Water Drop\" released', 'comic-series-mizu-a-talking-water-drop-released', 'news/2019/12/5e09c5c06e033.jpg', 'In October 2019, the comic series \"Mizu – A talking water drop\" was officially launched and came to a all children in Vietnam. The comic series were written...', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">In October 2019, the comic series \"Mizu &ndash; A talking water drop\" was officially launched and came to all children in Vietnam. The comic series were written and built based on educational content of \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\" program. The comic series were created by Suntory Holdings Limtied., Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage Co., Ltd., Central Council of the Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization, Kim Dong Publishers; including content design contributions by Mizuiku program team of SPVB.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 605px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/PN14.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br /><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 606px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/PN15.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br /><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 606px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/PN16.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em>Cover pages of 03 chapters</em></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;<br />Mizu is a cute and friendly water drop, the protagonist of the comic \"Mizu - A Talking Water Drop\". Mizu will let children understand about origin and importance role of water in life, analyzing the situation and causes of water pollution; and together with Mizu learn about ways to protect our water.<br /><br />The comic series uses easy-to-understand words and illustrations with lovely drawings suitable for children aged 04 years and over.<br /><br />In the comic, Mizu will reveal to children very interesting things about water such as: \"<em>Only 0.3% of the earth\'s water is exploit for drinking\" or \"Every day we need to drink from 2 to 3 liters of water to keep your body healthy</em> &rdquo; ... Sometimes Mizu helps children to answer cute questions like, \" <em>Why does the ice cube melt into water</em>? \" \"<em>What happens when the water is polluted</em>\" ... And Mizu will show you the ways to save and protect water very specifically, such as using vegetable cleaning water to water plants, when washing dishes to use just enough detergent, not playing with water balls ...</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 300px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/PN17.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em>The content in the comic series is depicted by lovely drawings</em></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;<br />These comic series became a meaningful gift of the MIZUIKU Program for children aged 4 to 10 who are children of company\'s employees on the occation of The World Habitat Day.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 849px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/PN018.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">The series will be used in educational activities of the program \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\", sold at bookstores of Kim Dong Publishing House and on Tiki.vn. The parents and children can read the comic to find out useful information about water resources and how to protect water resources. At the same time, each comic book sold will contribute 5,000 VND for meaningful activities of Mizuiku Program in the future.<br />&nbsp;<br /><em>(Mizuiku Program Team - I love clean water)</em></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 11, '0', '2019-10-18 05:01:00', 1, '2019-12-31 04:52:24', 1, '2019-12-31 04:52:24', NULL),
(183, 163, 4, 'Exciting Mizuiku Activity with School Wall Painting in Lang Son, Quang Nam, Ben Tre and Dong Nai Province', 'exciting-mizuiku-activity-with-school-wall-painting-in-lang-son-quang-nam-ben-tre-and-dong-nai-province', 'news/2019/12/5e09c687bd00c.jpg', 'With the responsibility and awareness of necessity for saving and preserving water resources, 17 elementary schools in Lang Son, Quang Nam, Ben Tre and Dong...', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">With the responsibility and awareness of necessity for saving and preserving water resources, 17 elementary schools in Lang Son, Quang Nam, Ben Tre and Dong Nai provinces participated in the activity of wall painting with topic related to content of \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\" program.<br /><br />The activity was organized in July and August 2019 by Suntory Holdings Ltd. Group, Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage (SPVB) in collaboration with Vietnam National Union of Students and Ho Chi Minh Communist Youth Union in the provinces. The wall paintings with the message of environment protection and water protection were carried out by more than 150 Green Summer volunteers from universities of Quang Nam, Dong Nai, Tien Giang and Thai Nguyen Province.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 450px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/PN009.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><em>Volunteers of Tien Giang University painted the walls in Ben Tre</em></span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;<br />Each painting was carefully sketched by volunteers; selecting all areas that were easily accessible to children for drawing such as classroom walls, corridors, toilets&hellip;. The image of Mizu was painted in both creative and aesthetic way, at the same time, the paintings clearly described the aim of the program on saving and protecting water resources.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 450px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/PN010.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em>Walls after painting at An Binh Tay Elementary School (Ba Tri District, Ben Tre Province)</em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">The paintings tell different stories about Mizu: Mizu and her friends watering the plants, Mizu instructing how to save water, Mizu making cleaning and protecting the environment... along with the slogan such as \"<em>Keep our school, our class: Green - Clean - Beautiful - Safe</em>\", \"<em>Protect precious water with Mizuiku</em>\", ...</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 450px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/PN011.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Mizu in paintings with environment and water protection messages</span></em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">At the beginning of the new school year, teachers are very excited because the schools have been decorated and become more beautiful, that will surely bring a lot of inspiration and joy to children in this new school year.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 450px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/PN012.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Wall painting in Lang Son</span></em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">In 2019, 17 elementary schools in Lang Son, Quang Nam, Ben Tre and Dong Nai provinces participated in \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\" program have organized many activities to raise children&rsquo;s awareness about saving and protecting water resources. Extracurricular activities on Recycling Day, SPVB Plant Tours, Trip to Forest will be conducted next so children will have more experience in applying and practicing their knowledge which they have been trained.<br />&nbsp;<br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><em>(Written by: &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; program team)</em></span></span></span></div>', 'news', 1, NULL, 6, 'en', 3, '0', '2019-09-06 03:40:00', 1, '2020-01-01 04:16:27', 33, NULL, NULL),
(184, 141, 4, 'Simple water-saving methods to guide children', 'simple-water-saving-methods-to-guide-children', 'news/2019/12/5e09cb89de8e7.jpg', 'Checking your home’s water system, using water economically, not littering indiscriminately are the simple but effective way that \"Mizuiku – I love clean...', '<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Checking your home&rsquo;s water system, using water economically, not littering indiscriminately are the simple but effective way that \"Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water\" </span></span></strong><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">project<strong> spread to the students.</strong></span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">In Vietnam, surface water of urban area (canals, ditches, rivers), surface water of rural areas (ponds, lakes, rivers), groundwater and seawater face negative impacts from human. The first cause of water shortage is the exploitation and overuse, not saving water in living and production.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;Clean water lessons which &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; project taught to students in grades 3-4 are simple ways for each child to apply in their own home.</span></span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Check your home&rsquo;s water system</span></span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">This method is relatively simple, can be deployed immediately to all members of the family. The purpose is to limit leakage, wastage of water. Parents can teach children to do this simple activity by holding a small game.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Specifically, each family can paste a track board to the indoor water system. Every member participates in exercising the track by observing the equipment is \"qualify\" or not and then mark the board. If the child is not able to read, we can use smiley face, sad face, angry face to easy to implement. For more excitement, parents may choose to award \"excellent employees\" every weekend or at the end of the month.</span></span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Wash hands properly to save water</span></span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Washing hands seems to be an act of losing only a small amount of water, but when children wash their hands improperly, too much time under the tap water can causes huge amounts of water, not use up and dropping out.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The 6-step hand-washing exercise and fun hand-washing dance became an interesting lesson on protecting clean water for more than 2,500 students in Ben Tre, Hanoi and Bac Ninh in the last May.</span></span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse;\" border=\"0\" width=\"624\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"center\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 624px; padding: 0in 5.4pt; vertical-align: bottom; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #555555;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 500px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/4(3).jpg\" alt=\"Nhung phuong phap tiet kiem nuoc don gian de huong dan tre hinh anh 1\" /></span></span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 624px; padding: 3.75pt 0in 6pt; vertical-align: bottom; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #555555;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Students in Thanh Oai (Hanoi) learn about 6 proper hand-washing steps through hand-washing dance</span></span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Step 1: Wet the hands, take 3 &ndash; 5ml of liquid hand wash or rub the soap in the palm and the back of the hands. Rub hands palm to palm so that the soap is applied evenly</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Step 2: Place the right palm and fingers on the back of left hand and rub the dorsum and fingers (and vice versa)</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Step 3: Put one palm on the other, scrub the palms and between fingers</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Step 4: Hook the palms with backs of fingers to opposing palms with fingers interlocked, scrub the back of the fingers</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Step 5: Use one palm to rub rotationally the other thumb and vice versa</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Step 6: Clasp one hand&rsquo;s fingers and rub the tip in the other palm and vice versa. Rinse hand with water and use a clean tower to dry hands thoroughly</span></span><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse;\" border=\"0\" width=\"624\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"center\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 624px; padding: 0in 5.4pt; vertical-align: bottom; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #555555;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 500px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/5(2).jpg\" alt=\"Nhung phuong phap tiet kiem nuoc don gian de huong dan tre hinh anh 2\" /></span></span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 624px; padding: 3.75pt 0in 6pt; vertical-align: bottom; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #555555;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Students at Vinh An 2 Primary School, Ben Tre Province were trained on proper hand-washing methods to save water right after class.</span></span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The minimum time requirement for the whole process is 30 seconds, just enough for the children to wash their hands thoroughly, without wasting too much time and wasting water</span></span><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Utilize water for many purposes</span></span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Many people have the habit of using only water once for one purpose. Sometimes this leads to unnecessary waste. In severe hot weather, cutwater often occurs so that we should change this habit urgency.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Specifically, when washing dishes or vegetables, we should have a clean pot of water instead of washing directly under the tap. In this way, the water after washing can be used to irrigate plants, water the soil to reduce dust, reduce heat in the yard / balcony. The last wash (relatively clean) can be re-used to clean furniture or clean the floor.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">This way of saving water can be applied to both adults and children. However, a small note is that parents need to actively utilize water for many purposes so that young children are able to see it as the right thing to do, and to do it happily.</span></span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Do not litter indiscriminately</span></span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Garbage is one of the major causes of pollution. Some people think that throwing rubbish around the house does not affect the water. However, in the dry season, garbage will accumulate in the sewer\'s hatch; if not handled in time it will generate bacteria, pollute the environment. In the rainy season, garbage, hazardous waste will seal the sewer cover and lead to flooding. Frequent contact and movement under this condition will cause skin disease.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Next, the waste flows into the rivers, the sea, affecting the species living in the water environment. Contamination of river water leads to shortage of domestic water for people. Contamination or drought of water reservoirs causes serious consequences.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Therefore, at home, parents need to teach children to throw the garbage in the right place, collect and classify waste into organic waste and inorganic waste to contribute to environmental protection. At school, teachers may ask children to clean the classroom and the playground. This not only helps to keep the hygiene of the common space but also tightens the friendship. Combining school-to-home education helps children recognize this is the right thing to do.</span></span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse;\" border=\"0\" width=\"624\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"center\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 624px; padding: 0in 5.4pt; vertical-align: bottom; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #555555;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 500px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/6(1).jpg\" alt=\"Nhung phuong phap tiet kiem nuoc don gian de huong dan tre hinh anh 3\" /></span></span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 624px; padding: 3.75pt 0in 6pt; vertical-align: bottom; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #555555;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Combining school-to-home education helps children understand the importance of keeping the environment clean.</span></span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Share your knowledge with friends</span></span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Once your child has memorized and continued the ways to protect the water, do not forget to tell your child to share these knowledge to their loved ones, their friends and the community. There will not be much practical sense if a defender has a saboteur. Let children understand how much the value and strength of the community can increase the effectiveness of this activity.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The above methods are introduced in the curriculum of <u>\"Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water\"</u> carried out by Suntory Holdings Limited (Japan), Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage, in coordination with Vietnam Central Council of Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization, Vietnam National Union of Student, and endorsement of the Ministry of Education and Training.</span></span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse;\" border=\"0\" width=\"624\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"center\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 624px; padding: 0in 5.4pt; vertical-align: bottom; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #555555;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 448px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/7.jpg\" alt=\"Nhung phuong phap tiet kiem nuoc don gian de huong dan tre hinh anh 4\" /></span></span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 624px; padding: 3.75pt 0in 6pt; vertical-align: bottom; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #555555;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Children of Tan Thieng B Primary School learn about water and the cycle of water.</span></span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The goal is to foster children\'s basic awareness and daily routines on the importance of water, the cycle of water, the sense of protection and saving of water resources. This is a sustainable solution for the next generation to act for environment.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">From May 13<sup>th</sup> to May 23<sup>rd</sup>, the program organizers had opened more than 60 classes for 2 modules: \"What happened with the water?\" And \"What can we do?\" for more than 900 students at schools in Ben Tre: Thanh Hai, My An, Tan Thieng B, Vinh An and An Hoa Tay 2 under the instruction of a team of teachers including teachers in charge of Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization and teachers in grades 3-4. Familiar lessons are taught through hands-on learning method, playing and learning. Intuitive and interactive learning methods such as group discussions, Q &amp; A, games, case studies, etc. are skillfully used to convey lectures.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">\"Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water\" project was launched in 2015 with many remarkable activities such as organizing more than 400 classes for around 5,000 students, 16 Water Festivals for over 7,700 students, renovation and construction of water filtration systems and restrooms for over 16 schools participated in the project</span></span><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">.&nbsp;</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">This year, the project will expand to 30 primary schools in Bac Ninh, Hanoi, Ho Chi Minh City and Ben Tre. Activities include TOTs; Mizuiku classes, Water Festivals and SPVB plant tours; supporting the maintenance of environmental education at participated schools in 2015-2016 and encouraging the expansion of the beneficiary area by 2017 by donating teaching and learning materials developed by the project. The project also constructs clean water facilities in primary schools and in the community.</span></span>&nbsp;<br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Since 2017, Suntory Holdings Limited (Japan), Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage, in coordination with Vietnam Central Council of Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization, Vietnam National Union of Student, and endorsement of the Ministry of Education and Training to set up the goal of expanding the program nationwide, completing the Mizuiku teaching and learning materials to become the official reference books in primary education allowed by the Ministry of Education and Training, developing the online learning (E-learning) and Website Mizuiku - I love clean water. Visit <u><span style=\"color: #007197;\">facebook.com/mizuikuemyeunuocsach</span></u></span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">to update the latest information on the project.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #111111;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Giang Thu Quan</span></span></span></strong></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 7, '0', '2018-03-21 02:18:00', 1, '2019-12-30 10:04:22', 1, NULL, NULL),
(185, 142, 4, 'Youth energy of green summer along the journey \"2017 Mizuiku - I love clean water\"', 'youth-energy-of-green-summer-along-the-journey-2017-mizuiku-i-love-clean-water', 'news/2019/12/5e09cc1565997.jpg', 'This summer, the trainers of the Green Summer voluntary campaign took up a new responsibility as the ambassadors of the \"2017 Mizuiku – I love clean...', '<h2 style=\"margin-top: 3.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"color: #5f5f5f;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">This summer, the trainers of the Green Summer voluntary campaign took up a new responsibility as the ambassadors of the \"2017 Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; program, besides their traditional voluntary activities. The ambassadors joined hands to spread the message and knowledge on water resource protection to over 700 students in Ben Tre, Thanh Oai (Hanoi) and Bac Ninh Provinces of Vietnam.</span></span></span></h2>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">The trainers of the Green Summer voluntary campaign are specially trained to protect water resources</span></span></strong><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Images of students all around the country wearing a blue shirt, eager to a new land to give youth has long been a memorable photo for a hot summer. This year, on this meaningful journey, more than 30 trainers of Green Summer in fronts such as Ben Tre, Thanh Oai (Hanoi) and Bac Ninh also carry on another mission: conveying knowledge on protecting valuable water resources by the \"Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water\" project to students.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">The \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\" project was launched in 2015 in Vietnam by Suntory Holdings Limited, Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage. In 2017, in coordination with Vietnam Central Council of Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization, Vietnam National Union of Student, and endorsement of the Ministry of Education and Training, the project has been helping to build awareness of the importance of water and to foster the habit of saving water every day in children as a sustainable solution to save resources and protect the environment.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Throughout the training sessions for the Green Summer trainers conducted by the Tuong Lai Center and the Live &amp; Learn Center held in July, teachers directly participated in environmental education classes to bring about simple but practical knowledge to nearly 700 students in areas that are frequently exposed to water shortages and pollution such as Ba Tri District, Cho Lach (Ben Tre), Thanh Oai (Hanoi) ... in the journey \"2017 Mizuiku - I love clean water\".</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">This year, the project has a close cooperation with the Green Summer campaign, starting with training sessions, fostering skills for more than 30 trainers in Ho Chi Minh City and Hanoi. In addition to be equipped with knowledge about the importance of water to life and the role of propaganda for students, Green Summer trainers also experience real-life water savings such as checking your home\'s water system, 6 proper hand-washing steps, using water economically, not littering indiscriminately around your home, lakes, rivers, streams ... or activities such as \"Understanding of water cycle\"; \"Hand-washing dance\"; \"I am water\" rhetoric, etc.</span></span></p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\"><img style=\"width: 641px; height: 480px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/8.jpg\" alt=\"Mỗi chiến sỹ M&ugrave;a H&egrave; Xanh l&agrave; những đại sứ truyền tải kiến thức nước sạch trong h&agrave;nh tr&igrave;nh &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; Em y&ecirc;u nước sạch&rdquo; 2017\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Each Green Summer trainer is an ambassador for conveying knowledge of clean water in the journey \"2017 Mizuiku - I love clean water\" </span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Participating in the Green Summer for three consecutive years, Nguyen Van An - Cao Thang Technical College shared: \"Only coming to the land &ldquo;thirsty&rdquo; of clean water like Thanh Phu District (Ben Tre) helped me understand deeply about the scarcity of clean water there. I feel \"very useful\" when directly participating with the Green Summer trainers to convey the basic knowledge about clean water to the children in the journey \"2017 Mizuiku - I love clean water\".</span></span><br /><strong><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Volunteer to convey knowledge to children</span></span></strong><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Applying the \"Learner-centered\" teaching method of the \"Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water\" project in lectures at schools, more than 30 Green Summer trainers have flexibly utilized their knowledge and skills to build lecture contents appropriating to the circumstances of each participating locality. With the enthusiasm of the trainers, the summer classes in Ben Tre, Thanh Oai and Hanoi took place actively and received the active support of local people.</span></span></p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\"><img style=\"width: 641px; height: 480px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/9.jpg\" alt=\"Sự nhiệt t&igrave;nh th&ecirc;̉ hi&ecirc;̣n rõ tr&ecirc;n từng nét mặt c&aacute;c chiến sỹ M&ugrave;a H&egrave; Xanh nhằm truyền tải những kiến thức về nước sạch gần gũi nhất đến c&aacute;c em học sinh\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">The enthusiasm is reflected in each face of the Green Summer trainers to convey the knowledge of clean water to the students.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Trainer Van An also added: \"For teaching activities and group activities, games are an effective way to approach environmental education. The interactive activities we create for children will help them memorize longer and apply in their own home and school&rdquo;.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">At summer classes, students are more interested in taking part in visual classes with the guidance of university students. Huynh Le Thuy Duong, a student of grade 5.2 of An Hoa Tay 1 Primary School (Ba Tri District, Ben Tre Province) enthusiastically shared: \"After attending Mizuiku class, I will not throw waste into the river and let the tap run when washing hands&rdquo;.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">In &ldquo;2017 Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; project, the Green Summer trainers also participated in upgrading clean water facilities in key schools such as installing water filtration systems and restrooms at 10 primary schools in Ben Tre such as Tan Thieng B (Cho Lach, Ben Tre), My An (Thanh Phu, Ben Tre) and a public project in Cu Lao An Binh, An Hiep Commune, Ba Tri District.</span></span><br />&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;<br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">In particular, the trainers also joined the teachers and students involved in painting wall decoration around the facilities to prepare for a new school year more colorful and exciting.</span></span></p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\"><img style=\"width: 641px; height: 480px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/10(1).jpg\" alt=\"Hành đ&ocirc;̣ng thi&ecirc;́t thực của các chi&ecirc;́n sỹ Mùa Hè Xanh tại địa phương\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Practical action of Green Summer trainers at local</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Youth energy, enthusiasm of the trainers of the Green Summer coupled with the journey \"2017 Mizuiku - I love clean water\" has contributed to spreading the spirit of \"I love clean water\" to the localities throughout the country of Vietnam.</span></span><br /><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">Originating from Japanese, Mizu means \"water\" and iku means \"education\". \"Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water\" is a project to propagate and educate the sense of protection of water resources. \"2017 Mizuiku - I love clean water\" is being implemented nationwide with the strategic cooperation between Suntory Holdings Limited (Japan), Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage, in coordination with Vietnam Central Council of Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization, Vietnam National Union of Student, and endorsement of the Ministry of Education and Training, \"Mizuiku - I love clean water \" is a highly meaningful educational communication program for educating children about the important role of water resources on the Earth. In the coming months, a number of useful activities will be implemented such as: Upgrading water facilities at schools, the Water Festival, the national painting competition on water topics, and a tour to the Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam plant for students from primary schools participating in the project.</span></span></p>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 5, '0', '2018-03-21 02:22:00', 1, '2019-12-30 10:07:02', 1, NULL, NULL),
(186, 148, 4, 'Opening Ceremony of “Mizuiku – I Love Clean Water” 2018', 'opening-ceremony-of-mizuiku-i-love-clean-water-2018', 'news/2019/12/5e09ccfb62db7.jpg', 'On the occasion of World’s Water Day (March 22), Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage (Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam) in collaboration with the Central Council of...', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">On the occasion of World&rsquo;s Water Day (March 22), Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage (Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam) in collaboration with the Central Council of Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization and Vietnam National Union of Student hosted the Opening Ceremony of &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; program 2018 in Quang Nam province. The opening ceremony had the attendance of senior dignitaries from the local authorities and local partners, senior representatives from Suntory Holdings and Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam, teachers and students of Quang Nam province. &nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 450px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/DSCN6394.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><em>On-stage kick-off ceremony joined by representatives of co-organizers and high-ranking guests with students&nbsp;</em></span></span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The Education Program for Nature and Water &ndash; Mizuiku &ndash; is an initiative of Suntory Holdings Limited (Suntory) which was established and implemented in Japan since 2004. Since then, the program has attracted the participation of over 145,000 pupils and parents and was considered amongst the most successful programs that Suntory has conducted for the Japanese community and society. In 2015, Suntory successfully launched the program in the Northern region of Vietnam in collaboration with Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam and the local partners. The program was tailored so that it is suitable for the reality in Vietnam.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The year of 2017 marked a milestone for the program with the strategic partnership between Suntory, Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam, and the Central Council of Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization, the Vietnam National Student Union, together with education-insight expertise from the Live &amp; Learn and Tuong Lai Centre and the endorsement of the Ministry of Education &amp; Training. The program has expanded nationwide providing trainings to teachers of 30 elementary schools amongst which 14 elementary schools implemented teaching classes for students in Bac Ninh province, Hanoi, Ho Chi Minh City and Ben Tre province and achieved impressive results. In particular, the program has conducted 10 Training for the Trainers (TOT) courses on water conservation and preservation education for over 260 teachers and volunteers; more than 265 classes on water education for over 5,000 elementary students; constructing 13 clean water facilities nationwide including RO water filtration systems and upgrading restrooms. Besides, 10 Water Knight Festivals for over 3,900 students and teachers and 10 plant tours to Suntory PepsiCo plants for over 1,200 students and teachers were also successfully facilitated. After the launch in August, the &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; drawing contest for children has received more than 300,000 entries. In addition, the program has attracted 200 Suntory PepsiCo employees and students from Dynamic start-up competition through the series of sharing events on &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; program and CSR activities of Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam.</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 450px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/DSCN6486.JPG\" alt=\"\" /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><em>Ms Asuka Nakayama from Suntory Publicity Service Ltd. shared about Mizuiku program practices in Japan</em></span></span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">In 2018, the \"Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water\" program will be formally incorporated into the Joint Program between the Ministry of Education and Training and the Ho Chi Minh Central Communist Youth Union for the 2017-2018 academic year. The program will be implemented in Ha Giang, Lang Son, Ha Noi, Bac Ninh, Quang Nam and Ben Tre provinces. The new developments for 2018 will be the launch of &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; website featuring E-learning. In addition, there will also be a &ldquo;<em>Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; Artworks</em>&nbsp;contest for the children .</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 450px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/DSCN6425.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><em>A demonstration class of Mizuiku teaching program in Vietnam</em></span></span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">It is expected that the program will continue to receive good attention from the media agencies and newspapers so that it would reach more people in the community and society.&nbsp;</span></span></div>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 134, '0', '2018-04-02 10:51:00', 1, '2019-12-30 10:11:00', 1, NULL, NULL);
