(187, 147, 4, '70 teachers participating in “Mizuiku – I love clean water” training course in Ben Tre and Quang Nam province', '70-teachers-participating-in-mizuiku-i-love-clean-water-training-course-in-ben-tre-and-quang-nam-province', 'news/2019/12/5e09cdb614d6f.jpg', 'On April 22, 2018, Suntory Holdings Limited, Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage (Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam) in collaboration with the Central Council of Ho Chi...', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">On April 22, 2018, Suntory Holdings Limited, Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage (Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam) in collaboration with the Central Council of Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization and Ben Tre Youth Union organized the&nbsp; &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; TOT (training for the trainers) class for 35 teachers including head teachers of school young pioneer unit and form teachers of 5 beneficiary elementary schools which are Bao Thuan, My Hoa (Ba Tri district), Giao Thanh, Thanh Phong A, and Thanh Phong B (Thanh Phu district).</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 450px; height: 334px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/24-4-QuangNamBenTre.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br /><em><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Teacher demonstrates &ldquo;River in my hometown&rdquo; activity</span></span></em></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Special guests attending the opening ceremony were Lam Nhu Quynh, Deputy Secretary of Ben Tre Youth Union, representatives of Central Council of Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization, Ben Tre Department of Education and Training, and Suntory PepsiCo Viet Nam.<br /><br />The training program lasted for two days (April 21- 22) covering interactive teaching methods and skills for environmental education and extracurricular activities on water topics under the Mizuiku curriculum. In particular, it consists of the importance of environmental education, &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; program introduction, practice of learning activities in the curriculum.<br /><br />Phan Van Vu, an outstanding head teacher of school young pioneer unit of Ben Tre, excitedly shared: \"The training class is fun, useful and provides lots of interesting knowledge for us to teach our students\". In May, teachers will organize Mizuiku classes for all third and fourth grade students from beneficiary schools with supervision from educational partners and teaching materials support from the organizer of the \"Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water\" program. With the enthusiasm of the teachers, Mizuiku&rsquo;s spirit will continue to spread to many beloved students.</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 450px; height: 333px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/24-4-QuangNamBenTre1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br /><em><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Group discussion for school presentation practice</span></span></em></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Prior on April 14-15, 2018, the same training class was hosted in Quang Nam province for 35 teachers there. Through the training, teachers learned and practiced the water saving and protection knowledge and the student-centered teaching method of the \"Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water\" program.</strong></span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><img style=\"width: 450px; height: 328px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/24-4-QuangNamBenTre2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Teachers practice &ldquo;I am water&rdquo; role play&nbsp; </span></span></em></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<table style=\"width: 500px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" align=\"center\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #66ffff;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Founded by Suntory Holdings Limited (Japan), in 2018, the &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; program will be organized in Ha Giang, Quang Nam, Ben Tre and Lang Son province. The &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; program aims to educate and raise awareness among primary school students on the importance of water resource and the ways in which we can conserve clean water, through providing practical knowledge of water saving and protection, and also upgrading, constructing clean water facilities for schools.</span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 9, '0', '2018-04-24 07:36:00', 1, '2019-12-30 10:13:55', 1, NULL, NULL),
(188, 151, 4, 'Training of Trainees (TOT) for Green Summer Volunteers in Danang on June 23 – 24, 2018', 'training-of-trainees-tot-for-green-summer-volunteers-in-danang-on-june-23-24-2018', 'news/2019/12/5e09d0ca74bfe.jpg', 'On June 23, 2018, , in collaboration between Vietnam Union Student, Central Council of Ho Chi Minh young pioneer organization, and Suntory Pepsico Vietnam...', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">On June 23, 2018, , in collaboration between Vietnam Union Student, Central Council of Ho Chi Minh young pioneer organization, Suntory Pepsico Vietnam Beverage,and Future Center, an Opening of Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water 2018 - Opening Ceremony was held for Green Summer volunteers in Danang University of Pedagogy &ndash; Danang city, who will participate in teaching for children of residential areas in Quang Nam Province.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 369px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/Picture1-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Mr. Nguyen Thai An - Deputy Head of Youth Union&rsquo;s Department for Young Children was making a speech in Opening Ceremony of the TOT<br /><br />The TOT lasted for 2 days 23 &ndash; 24 June 2018. There were 30 students, came from universities and colleges within Danang city, participated in this TOT. Main content include: improving appropriate teaching skill to proceed environmental education and outdoor activities about water, according to lesson plan of Mizuiku program. Besides the volunteers were able to learn more about Mizuiku program, the critical rope of environmental education, as well as learn and practice teaching as lesson plan. </span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 374px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/DSCN1088.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">In 2018, the program was held along with many activities in Ha Giang, Quang Nam, Ben Tre, Lang Son. With this TOT, Mizuiku Program will improve social awareness and responsibility of environmental protection, clean water protection in schools for students; instruct and provide for trainees basic knowledge about clean water usage. By which, can contribute for students&rsquo; education of environmental self-awareness, saving pure water, decrease water contamination nowadays.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 411px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/DSCN1123.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 413px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/Picture3-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></span><br /><br />&nbsp;</div>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 23, '0', '2018-07-09 10:34:00', 1, '2019-12-30 10:26:41', 1, NULL, NULL),
(189, 152, 4, '100 children visit Suntory Pepsico\'s Cantho & Dongnai Plant', '100-children-visit-suntory-pepsico-s-cantho-dongnai-plant', 'news/2019/12/5e09d13f48931.jpg', 'To spread the meaningful message of the Mizuiku program on water conservation and preservation with the aim of creating cohesion, pride for employees and...', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">To spread the meaningful message of the Mizuiku program on water conservation and preservation with the aim of creating cohesion, pride for employees and their children, their families when they are members of Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverages Company Limited, the company creates an opportunity for them to visit the factory, learn about the company, production process&hellip; and waste water treatment process, reuse of water in order to show the social responsibility for caring, protecting our environment as well as water sources, especially, organizing Mizuiku class.<br /><br />On 07th July 2018 and 14th July 2018, 100 children who are the children of employees at Can Tho, Dong Nai factories, Sales Department Can Tho Branch as well as Ho Chi Minh Branch had visited the factory of Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Co., Ltd in Can Tho and Dong Nai and attended \"Mizuiku Classroom &ndash; I Love Clean Water\".</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 366px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/IMG_1656.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></span>Children visited the factory of Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Co., Ltd in Can Tho.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">This is one of the activities organized by Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage Co., Ltd with the desire to create more cohesion, pride and love about the Company for employees&rsquo; children.<br /><br />Especially, at this class, they participated in the Mizuiku class which was taught by the Mizuiku delegates &ndash; they are also the staffs of Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam and students of the \"DYNAMIC &ndash; The future businessman/woman&rdquo; by bringing useful knowledge through interactive activities.<br /><br />Let&rsquo;s watching the exciting moments of this experience!</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 366px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/IMG_1293.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Children give a warm welcome to delegates.<br /><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 366px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/IMG_1295.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">They listen carefully what the company&rsquo;s representative is sharing.<br /><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 366px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/IMG_3983.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;They are very exciting to share their ideas<br /><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 366px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/IMG_3989.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;The delegates of Mizuiku stir up the classroom, organizing many meaningful educational games to educate the importance of water conservation and preservation.<br /><br /><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 328px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/IMG_1711.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Presents for children at the program<br /><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 366px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/IMG_4227.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;They feel very excited with activities of the visit<br /><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 366px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/IMG_3934.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;The children are happy to welcome the delegates to enjoy this class<br /><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 374px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/IMG_3849.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Memorable moments at the factory Suntory Pepsico&ndash; Dong Nai Branch<br /><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 334px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/IMG_3836.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;They have a meaningful visit to the factory</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 1320, '0', '2018-08-08 10:15:00', 1, '2019-12-31 01:57:36', 1, NULL, NULL),
(190, 153, 4, 'Mizuiku Classroom of the Green Summer Soldiers 2018', 'mizuiku-classroom-of-the-green-summer-soldiers-2018', 'news/2019/12/5e0aaa9320520.jpg', 'In summer 2018, more than 40 voluntary students of the Green Summer campaign participated in the training course called “Mizuiku – I love clean water” in...', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">In summer 2018, more than 40 voluntary students of the Green Summer campaign participated in the training course called &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; in HCMC and Lang Son.<br /><br />Students received not only the knowledge of the importance of water resources in life, the current water resources status and human actions that can change the pollution status, scarcity of the current water resources, contributing to preserving clean water for future generations. These contents are transmitted through close lessons and highly interactive activities such as water filter experiments, educational animated films, group discussions to learn about the water cycle, hand-washing dance, relay games.v.v..<br /><br />This is also the second consecutive year of the \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\" program, which is accompanied by Green Summer soldiers to organize educational classes on water and environment protection for children in disadvantaged areas in Lang Son and Ben Tre Province. So far, more than 500 children have participated in the exciting activities of the classes and received the Mizuiku Kit document to memorize knowledge better.</span></span></div>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; background-color: #eeeeee; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><img style=\"border: none; transform: rotate(0.00rad); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad);\" src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/Cxj2b8crCZMOhz08UCa14EP-Y8C_GAU5XD_siqBHh19esqse2ykdVpN5qMLqSNgr_qJ62E9rcNs-epfASKjj2_hEV2nR9kUtP15mtN0E_dD2hx2CaEgKMEMQK0FR-upOG7wy_F1Ck78B0NLTxQ\" width=\"602\" height=\"451\" /></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6.9pt; background-color: #eeeeee; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Green Summer Soldiers of the Ho Chi Minh City University of Culture taught the class \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\" 2018 in Ba Tri District, Ben Tre Province</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; background-color: #eeeeee; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><img style=\"border: none; transform: rotate(0.00rad); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad);\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/gWsx_hvBq3weseI7fzYiUelHpVppyc8BOw91agneokh7sJTVE0VL9s7B4KkhvsbiW-WHWK5bQi_bJY36N_GB5_S9TK-3tQH3pZaVhNqZ2ADssB2Ui_wklhnJhGHZFUDg5TrWOx4o__3YmWBc9A\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" /></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6.9pt; background-color: #eeeeee; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Class \"Mizuiku - I love water\" 2018 of Cao Thang Technical College in Thanh Phu district, Ben Tre province</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6.9pt; background-color: #ffffff; text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Along with educational and fun activities, the program &ldquo;Mizuiku - I love water&rdquo; in 2018 also installed 15 water purification systems in 15 primary schools participating in the program in 4 provinces of Ha Giang, Lang Son, Quang Nam and Ben Tre, these are areas where water scarcity is occured. Some schools are still using unprocessed rainwater and students have to bring their own drinking water when they go to school, therefore, the system of drinking water purifier on site is a practical solution.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br />Especially, the volunteers together with teachers and students involved in painting wall decoration around the facilities to prepare for a new school year more colorful, exciting.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; background-color: #eeeeee; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><img style=\"border: none; transform: rotate(0.00rad); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad);\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/TNfIzATqqCRP62PD-2PiAjhAUZblBV5hdDH1wD4JW4SF3n2GiDIF8KPAvBpXx_FqmrcjxPk7FvXlsGa4MA3i8D5pedxcPu-gA5Rv4ZFa4F4TTRXDAJebxGy29xGdUVnAnCbhAxhOfUzb35l0-A\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6.9pt; background-color: #eeeeee; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Green Summer Soldiers of University of Medicine and Pharmacy at Ho Chi Minh City did painting at Bao Thuan Primary School (Ba Tri, Ben Tre)</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7.05pt; background-color: #ffffff; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7.05pt; background-color: #ffffff; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><img style=\"border: none; transform: rotate(0.00rad); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad);\" src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/Gb66pqNR_pt3GyS0FXw4kQReE5gL8f-lxxv7L_973JWBJ8aVn178v_qdfloxkTxRsggZllInOu1_61Qp_s9JsTcWOgI9IN6CUnd_aqSQrbQx3U5FHqg3DUUPdfgGTaslWmTNuCCVF--3hCEVRw\" width=\"634\" height=\"423\" /></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6.9pt; background-color: #eeeeee; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Green Summer Soldiers of Cao Thang Technical College at Giao Thanh Primary School (Thanh Phu, Ben Tre)</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6.9pt; background-color: #eeeeee; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><img style=\"border: none; transform: rotate(0.00rad); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad);\" src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/zOfu6VWFQi67xtBlstDP-zObKyj5ZG50NqTtaEGJIbuHtuoj9k3wz6XxTEJ4vIOEFS9L5He_NYxRdG0s_lTcxhRElw7DDVU4pPA3GFIhgGkjqO2LriCu8mHfxWQ3ubddJIhClAc9ANVQ5sgISA\" width=\"602\" height=\"401\" /></span> </span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6.9pt; background-color: #eeeeee; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Green Summer Soldiers of University of Medicine and Pharmacy at Ho Chi Minh City did painting at Bao Thuan Primary School (Ba Tri, Ben Tre)</span></span></span></p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">After attending the training course at the program, Nguyen Thi Viet Anh, 4th year student of Ho Chi Minh City University of Culture said: I had more extremely precious teaching experiences; the training course helped me acquire skills in conveying information and communication; especially, it helps me be confident to demonstrate my ability to speak in front of the crowd. She also said that: The propagation of water protection for children should be widespread, which will help them become more aware of water resources, protect their health and preserve the environment.</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: right;\"><br /><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Image source: Student Association of Cao Thang Technical College, Student Association of the University of Medicine and Pharmacy at Ho Chi Minh City</span></span></div>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 1344, '0', '2018-09-26 09:30:00', 1, '2019-12-31 03:30:10', 1, NULL, NULL),
(191, 154, 4, 'LAUNCH OF THE WATER CONSERVATION EDUCATION IDEA CONTEST AND CHILDREN PAINTING “MIZUIKU – I LOVE CLEAN WATER” CONTEST IN 2018', 'launch-of-the-water-conservation-education-idea-contest-and-children-painting-mizuiku-i-love-clean-water-contest-in-2018', 'news/2019/12/5e0ac16142477.jpg', 'On September 20, at the Dich Vong B Primary School in Cau Giay District, Hanoi, the Central Team Council, the Ministry of Education and Training, Suntory...', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">On September 20, at the Dich Vong B Primary School in Cau Giay District, Hanoi, Ho Chi Minh Central Council for Young Pioneers Organization, the Ministry of Education and Training, Suntory Holdings Limited, Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage jointly organized the Kick-off ceremony of \"Mizuiku &ndash; I Love Clean Water\" painting contest and E-learning course launching with the participation of nearly 1,300 children.<br /><br />Participants included: Mr. Nguyen Pham Duy Trang, Member of the Standing Committee, Head of the Youth Union of the Central Executive Committee, Vice Chairman of&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Ho Chi Minh Central Council for Young Pioneers Organization</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">; Mr. Nguyen Thai An, Member of the Central Executive Committee, Deputy Head of the Youth Union of the Central Executive Committee, Vice Chairman of&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Ho Chi Minh Central Council for Young Pioneers Organization</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">, representatives of Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage - Mr. Le Mac Linh, Vice President of Corporate Affairs and Communications; Ms. Chung Huong Giang,&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Corporate Affairs Manager</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;- Managing Corporate Social Responsibility; representative of the Ministry of Education and Training; Live &amp; Learn Center; school representatives, other delegates and media units.</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 500px; height: 347px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/2070.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">Representatives of the organizing committee of the program and children pressed the launch button of the ceremony</span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">The water conservation education idea contest and children painting \"Mizuiku &ndash; I Love Clean Water\" contest aims to further enhance the propaganda and education for children on rising awareness of protection of the environment and the water resource and is a playground for children to promote their creativity, express their ideas, talents, thoughts on clean water and use of clean water through paintings. At the same time, this is also an opportunity for teachers and volunteering students who have accessed to the \"Mizuiku &ndash; I Love Clean Water\" program to contribute to the development of educational programs of water resource protection for pupils with creative, practical and effective ideas.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 500px; height: 350px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/1939.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">Children participating in the contest</span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Mr. Le Mac Linh,&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Vice President of Corporate Affairs and Communications</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;of Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverag said at the launching ceremony: \"Mizuiku Painting Contest\" 2018 is for primary school children nationwide to further enhance the awareness of protection of the environment and the water resource and is a playground for children to promote their creativity, express their ideas, talents, thoughts on clean water and use of clean water through paintings. At the same time, this is also an opportunity for teachers and volunteering students who have accessed to the \"Mizuiku &ndash; I Love Clean Water\" program to contribute to the development of educational programs of water resource protection for pupils with creative, practical and effective ideas.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 500px; height: 341px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/2030.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">The painting contest is for children from 6 to 15 years old who are living, studying nationwide. Children participate in the painting contest should stick to the theme of \"Mizuiku &ndash; I Love Clean Water\", the meaning of clean water for life; actions to protect the water resource; criticize activities that lack of awareness, wastage, pollution of water resources; encourage practical actions to protect water resources; children\'s actions for thrifty, efficient use and protection of water resources; In particular, encourage the Councils of the provinces and cities to propagandize and organize the children with the ability and aspirations to participate in the contest.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 500px; height: 364px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/2149.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">Children participated in the painting contest at the launching ceremony</span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">During the launching ceremony, delegates and children drew pictures with the theme of protecting and using clean water &ndash; precious resources. In addition, the Organizing Committee has opened, introduced to participants the online education and training program of water conservation (e-learning) on http: // mizuiku-emyeunuocsach.vn. &nbsp;</span></span><br /><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 500px; height: 348px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/2130.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Representative of the Central Team Council and Suntory PepsiCo Beverage Vietnam Co., Ltd. together with children completed the painting of environment protection at the launching ceremony.</span></span></span><br /><br />In addition, the \"Mizuiku &ndash; I Love Clean Water\" program also launched the E-learning online course and the Water Conservation Education Idea Contest for teachers and volunteering students. After participating in the training of the program content, through the course teachers and volunteering students developed a syllabus for children\'s education about the importance of clean water for the environment and life of human; children\'s education about the protection of clean water; convey the message of criticizing activities that lack of awareness, wastage, pollution of water resources; Encourage, inspire the activities of water resources protection.</span></span><br /><br />\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><img style=\"width: 450px; height: 305px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/Untitled.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Teachers of Dich Vong B primary school participated in the MIZUIKU E-learning online course</span></span></span></span></span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<table style=\"width: 500px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" align=\"center\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Some specific information about the Contest<br />Contest time: from September 20 to the end of November 2018.</strong></span></span></div>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>1. Participants</strong><br /><br /><strong>- Water conservation education idea contest:</strong> Teachers and volunteering students participated in \"Mizuiku &ndash; I Love Clean Water\" program from 2015 to the present. Elementary and middle school teachers participated in the training course and are certified to complete the online training program E-learning on the website http://mizuiku-emyeunuocsach.vn.<br /><br />Participants will write an outline describing educational activities on water conservation, typed on A4 size, including: Objectives of the activity; beneficiaries; deployment time; Detailed description of educational activities.<br /><strong>- Children painting contest: </strong>children from 6 to 15 years old who are living, studying in the Children House System nationwide. Entries are drawn on A3 size white paper with selected colors such as lead, pigment, crayon, oil paint, watercolor, colored marker or other materials.</span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<br /><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 16, '0', '2018-09-26 03:44:00', 1, '2019-12-31 03:34:19', 1, NULL, NULL),
(192, 192, 2, 'Hoạt động học tập và trải nghiệm thiên nhiên thực tế lần đầu tiên được tổ chức tại Việt Nam.', 'hoat-dong-hoc-tap-va-trai-nghiem-thien-nhien-thuc-te-lan-dau-tien-duoc-to-chuc-tai-viet-nam', 'news/2019/12/5e0ac3a99f4db.jpg', 'Trong hai ngày 20 - 21/10/2018 vừa qua, tập đoàn Suntory Holdings Limited, Công ty TNHH nước giải khát Suntory PepsiCo Việt Nam cùng tỉnh đoàn Hà...', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Trong hai ng&agrave;y 20 - 21/10/2018 vừa qua, tập đo&agrave;n Suntory Holdings Limited, C&ocirc;ng ty TNHH nước giải kh&aacute;t Suntory PepsiCo Việt Nam, Hội Đồng Đội TƯ, c&ugrave;ng tỉnh đo&agrave;n H&agrave; Giang phối hợp tổ chức hoạt động d&atilde; ngoại thăm rừng, học t&acirc;p v&agrave; trải nghiệm thi&ecirc;n nhi&ecirc;n thực tế, thuộc khu&ocirc;n khổ Chương tr&igrave;nh Mizuiku - Em y&ecirc;u nước sạch 2018 cho 200 em học sinh tiểu học khối lớp 3, 4; c&aacute;n bộ, gi&aacute;o vi&ecirc;n, Tổng phụ tr&aacute;ch Đội của trường Tiểu học L&ecirc; Lợi,trường Tiểu học Trần Ph&uacute;, TP.H&agrave; Giang.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 362px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/193-600x395.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #0000cd;\"><em>C&aacute;c em học sinh c&ugrave;ng lưu giữ khoảnh khắc đ&aacute;ng nhớ c&ugrave;ng thầy c&ocirc; v&agrave; ban tổ chức</em></span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Chuyến tham quan học tập v&agrave; trải nghiệm thực tế trong thi&ecirc;n nhi&ecirc;n theo m&ocirc; h&igrave;nh chương tr&igrave;nh Mizuiku tại Nhật Bản lần đầu ti&ecirc;n được triển khai ở Việt Nam. Ng&agrave;y 20 v&agrave; 21.10 vừa qua, 200 em học sinh lớp 3 v&agrave; 4 đ&atilde; c&oacute; chuyến trải nghiệm thực tế trong rừng tại tỉnh H&agrave; Giang để t&igrave;m hiểu về bảo vệ rừng, bảo vệ m&ocirc;i trường, đặc biệt l&agrave; bảo vệ nguồn nước. C&aacute;c em được học về vai tr&ograve; giữ nước của lớp l&aacute; v&agrave; đất. C&aacute;c bạn được chia th&agrave;nh c&aacute;c nh&oacute;m nhỏ, tham quan quanh khu vực để cảm nhận về tầng địa sinh v&agrave; đưa ra nhận x&eacute;t với sự hướng dẫn của c&aacute;c chuy&ecirc;n gia v&agrave; gi&aacute;o vi&ecirc;n. C&aacute;c em sẽ được giới thiệu về th&aacute;c nước, tham gia c&aacute;c hoạt động t&igrave;m hiểu về c&aacute;c tầng thủy sinh quan s&aacute;t được tại th&aacute;c nước v&agrave; vẽ m&ocirc; phỏng tr&ecirc;n giấy hoặc thể hiện tr&ecirc;n chai nước v&agrave; thuyết tr&igrave;nh (tầng đ&aacute;y l&agrave; c&aacute;t, sỏi nhỏ, sỏi vừa, nước...), thực hiện c&aacute;c th&iacute; nghiệm về lọc nước, chơi c&aacute;c tr&ograve; chơi li&ecirc;n quan đến chủ đề m&ocirc;i trường,&hellip; </span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 367px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/IMG_7127.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><em>C&aacute;c bạn nhỏ rất h&agrave;o hứng với hoạt động độc đ&aacute;o v&agrave;o ng&agrave;y cuối tuần</em></span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 367px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/IMG_7150.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">C&aacute;c bạn học sinh được chia th&agrave;nh c&aacute;c nh&oacute;m, c&ugrave;ng trải nghiệm c&aacute;c hoạt động t&igrave;m hiểu về t&agrave;i nguy&ecirc;n nước, tầng địa sinh trong l&ograve;ng đất, chơi c&aacute;c tr&ograve; chơi li&ecirc;n quan đến m&ocirc;i trường&hellip;</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Chương tr&igrave;nh Mizuiku &ndash; Em y&ecirc;u nước sạch 2018, hoạt động học tập v&agrave; trải nghiệm thi&ecirc;n nhi&ecirc;n thực tế nhằm n&acirc;ng cao nhận thức của c&aacute;c em học sinh về vai tr&ograve; của t&agrave;i nguy&ecirc;n nước v&agrave; c&aacute;ch thức sử dụng hợp l&yacute; nguồn nước sạch, g&oacute;p phần bảo vệ nguồn nước v&agrave; rộng hơn l&agrave; m&ocirc;i trường sống xung quanh.<br /><br />Đồng thời, th&ocirc;ng qua chương tr&igrave;nh, tạo ra kh&ocirc;ng gian s&aacute;ng tạo, cơ hội thực h&agrave;nh v&agrave; s&acirc;n chơi đa dạng cho c&aacute;c em nhỏ nhằm k&iacute;ch th&iacute;ch &oacute;c quan s&aacute;t, &yacute; tưởng v&agrave; h&agrave;nh động của c&aacute;c em để bảo vệ nguồn nước n&oacute;i ri&ecirc;ng v&agrave; m&ocirc;i trường n&oacute;i chung.<br /><br />Chương tr&igrave;nh &ldquo;Mizuiku - Em y&ecirc;u nước sạch&rdquo; được tổ chức tại H&agrave; Giang hứa hẹn sẽ g&oacute;p phần mang đến những chuyển biến t&iacute;ch cực trong việc n&acirc;ng cao &yacute; thức về tiết kiệm v&agrave; bảo vệ nguồn nước sạch qu&yacute; gi&aacute; cho c&aacute;c em học sinh.</span></span><br /><br />&nbsp;</div>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'vi', 1735, '0', '2018-11-09 10:58:00', 1, '2020-01-01 22:25:10', 1, NULL, NULL),
(193, 192, 4, 'Mizuiku Outdoor activities in Ha Giang', 'mizuiku-outdoor-activities-in-ha-giang', 'news/2019/12/5e0ac45839175.jpg', 'During the two days of October 20 – October 21, 2018, Suntory Holdings Limited, Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverages, the Central Council of the Ho Chi Minh...', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">During the two days of October 20 &ndash; October 21, 2018, Suntory Holdings Limited, Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverages, the Central Council of the Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization and Youth Union of Ha Giang Province jointly organized a field trip to visit the forest, learn and experience the nature, under the framework of the 2018&nbsp; Mizuiku&ndash; I love Clean Water&nbsp; Program for 200 pupils of grade 3, 4; officers, teachers, the leader of young pioneer organization of&nbsp; Le Loi Primary School, Tran Phu Primary School of Ha Giang City.</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 362px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/193-600x395.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><em>The pupils share a memorable moment with the teachers and the organizers</em></span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">The study tour and practical experience in nature following the model of Mizuiku program in Japan was first implemented in Vietnam. On October 20 and 21, 200 pupils in grades 3 and 4 had a field trip to the forest in Ha Giang province to learn about forest protection, environmental protection, especially water resources protection. They learned about the water-holding role of leaves and soil. Pupils were divided into small groups, visiting around the area to feel the stratigraphy and making comments under the guidance of experts and teachers. They were introduced to the waterfalls, participating in activities to learn about the aquatic layers observed at the waterfall and drawing the simulations on paper or showing on water bottles and making presentations (the bottom had sand and small gravel, medium gravel, water ...), conducting experiments on water purification, playing games related to environmental topics, etc&hellip;</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 367px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/IMG_7127.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp; <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><em>The kids were excited about the unique activities at the weekend</em></span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 405px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/Untitled(1).jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><em>The pupils were divided into small groups, experiencing in the water resources, the stratigraphy of the soil, playing games related to environmental</em></span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><img src=\"/pic/News/images/Untitled1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"542\" height=\"348\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><em>Together observing the water filtration experiments conducted by the organizers</em></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">The 2018 Mizuiku &ndash; I love Clean Water Program, the learning and experiencing activities in the real nature to raise the awareness of pupils about the role of water resources and how to use clean water, helps to protect the water and, more broadly, the surrounding environment.<br /><br />At the same time, through the program, creating creative spaces, practice opportunities and a varied playground for children to stimulate their observations, ideas and actions to protect the water resources in particular and the environment in general.<br /><br />The program \"Mizuiku &ndash; I love Clean Water\" held in Ha Giang promises to contribute to bring positive changes in raising the awareness of pupils in saving and protecting the precious water.</span></span><br /><br />&nbsp;</div>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 1351, '0', '2018-11-09 05:11:00', 1, '2019-12-31 03:45:43', 1, NULL, NULL);
