(194, 156, 4, 'FACTORY TOUR WITH FULL OF EXPERIENCE OF MORE THAN 1,300 PUPILS FROM MIZUIKU PRIMARY SCHOOLS IN 2018', 'factory-tour-with-full-of-experience-of-more-than-1-300-pupils-from-mizuiku-primary-schools-in-2018', 'news/2019/12/5e0ac53c4f595.jpg', 'As part of the Mizuiku program –I love clean water in 2018, 13 trips for 3 primary schools in Lang Son, 5 primary schools in Quang Nam and 5 primary schools...', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">At three factories of Suntory Pepsico Vietnam in Bac Ninh, Quang Nam and Can Tho, the tour involved more than 1,300 pupils and more than 100 teachers, leaders of young pioneer organization of 13 schools benefited from the ProgramMizuiku - I love clean water in 2018.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 358px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/Untitled4.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">The pupils keep the moment together at Suntory Pepsico Vietnam factory</span></span></em></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">This activity helps children practical use the knowledge learned in the program, directly observe and learn about water saving activities and waste water treatment system in the production line of the factory.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 379px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/Untitled5.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em>&nbsp;Listening to the staffs at the factory about the water treatment process and water saving</em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">During the trip, children themselves were able to observe and experience the closed-loop technology to produce familiar beverage products in their daily life to understand more about the water saving and waste water treatment technologies of Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam; At the same time, they participated in many interesting activities such as: quiz, experiment on the role of water for the earth, experience of having lunch at the factory, etc.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 320px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/Untitled6.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;The pupils are excited to participate in the game, interacting with the staffs at the factory</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">This tour continued to leave a good impression with the pupils. Nguyen Bao Ngoc, Class 4C, Nguyen Du Primary School (Quang Nam) shared that: \"Through this program, I found it necessary to save water and love clean water source. I think the trip is very useful, interesting, what I like most is the water filtration experiments and the lunch experience at the factory&rsquo;s canteen\"</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 379px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/7(1).jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em>&nbsp;Lunch experience at the factory&rsquo;s canteen, self-taking and self-returning the food trays like workers in the factory</em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;<img style=\"width: 550px; height: 371px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/8(1).jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em>Nutritional meals after the fun playing moments</em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">As one of the teachers who directly lead the children to visit the factory, Ms. Tran Thi Thu Trang - Vice Principal of Ly Tu Trong Primary School (Quang Nam) was very excited about this extra-curricular activity: \"We are honored to be one of five primary schools in Quang Nam to receive&nbsp; the program [Mizuiku &ndash;I love clean water]. The school was not only trained teachers, organized classes for pupils, but also installed water filtration system for pupils to use daily. Especially, the actual tour program was organized at Quang Nam SPVB factory. I wish the program could be developed sustainability to have more practical activities for more pupils. \"</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 361px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/9(1).jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;<em>Little children are following the instructions of the staff, lined up to visit the production line</em></span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">An integral part of the success of the program is the positive contribution of staffs and departments in the factory. Mr. Nguyen Van Truc, Director of Quang Nam SPVB Factory, said that: \"Through the tour program, pupils learned more about the importance of clean water and the harm of environmental pollution, so that they will be more aware of water protection and saving, contributing to environmental protection not only in schools, but also throughout Vietnam.\"</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 343px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/10(2)(1).jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>The children not only experienced, learned about the precious water source, but also received the interesting gifts after the factory tour!</em><br /><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">The \"Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water\" program, through the student-centered education method, created creative spaces, opportunities for practice and varied playgrounds for children to stimulate their observations, ideas and actions to protect water resources in particular and the environment in general and their schools. Thank you the little children, teachers who always accompanied the \"Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water\" program!</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 3, '0', '2018-12-20 12:50:00', 1, '2019-12-31 03:50:00', 1, NULL, NULL),
(195, 155, 4, 'ORGANIZE RETRAINING FOR TEACHERS OF MIZUIKU SCHOOLS IN 2015-2017', 'organize-retraining-for-teachers-of-mizuiku-schools-in-2015-2017', 'news/2019/12/5e0ac5c54493e.jpg', 'To maintain the spirit and activities of the Mizuiku program – I love clean water in primary schools benefited from the program in 2015-2017, as well as...', '<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 359px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/Untitled(2).jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em>Delegates, teachers take collective photos</em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Participants in the training course were 35 source teachers who are the leader of young pioneer organization, homeroom teachers, working at 7 primary schools implementing the program from 2015 to 2017 including Thanh Mai Primary School, Do Dong Primary School, Phuong Trung Primary School, Kim Thu Primary School, Cao Duong Primary School, Cao Vien 2 Primary School, My Hung Primary School. The content of the training includes: fostering, repeating skills and active education methods and student-centered education method to implement environmental education activities and extracurricular activities on water topics under the curriculum of the Mizuiku program.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<img style=\"width: 550px; height: 436px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/Untitled1(1).jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em>Mr. Le Mac Linh, Vice President - Corporate Affairs, Suntory Pepsico Vietnam Beverage, spoke at the opening ceremony.</em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Participants of the program included: Mr. Le Mac Linh, Vice President - Corporate Affairs, Suntory Pepsico Vietnam Beverage</span></span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">; Mr. Nguyen Thai An, Member of Executive Board, Vice Chairman of the Central Council of the Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization; Mr. Bui Manh Huong, Deputy Director of Children\'s Affairs, Hanoi Youth Union; Mr. Nguyen Van Bong, deputy secretary of the district\'s cancellation; Mr. Nguyen Huy Diep, Member of Standing Committee of District Party Committee, Vice Chairman of Thanh Oai District People\'s Committee; Mr. Hoang Cong Khoa, district commissioner, Party Secretary, Chairman of People\'s Council; Mr. Pham Van Toan, Deputy Secretary of Party Committee, Chairman of Phuong Trung Commune People\'s Committee and representatives of Live &amp; Learn Center, etc.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 351px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/Untitled3.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;<em>The training took place at the People\'s Committee of Phuong Trung Commune, Thanh Oai District, Hanoi</em><br /><br />After attending the training, the teachers, the leader of young pioneer organization will be continued to be supported the teaching materials, continue to implement Mizuiku classes for pupils of other grades, helping the children raise the comprehensive wareness of water protection, contributing to environmental protection campaign around the world.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 6, '0', '2018-12-20 01:00:00', 1, '2019-12-31 03:53:22', 1, NULL, NULL),
(196, 157, 4, 'THE CLOSING CEREMONY OF “2018 MIZUIKU – I LOVE CLEAN WATER” PROGRAM', 'the-closing-ceremony-of-2018-mizuiku-i-love-clean-water-program', 'news/2019/12/5e0ac6a50b95c.jpg', 'On the morning of December 21, 2018, at Bao Thuan Primary School, Ba Tri District, Ben Tre Province, Suntory Holdings Limited Group, Suntory PepsiCo...', '<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 413px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/27-12.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em>Delegates at the closing ceremony took photos with the children who won prizes in the painting contest</em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Attending the closing ceremony were Mr. Takenobu Shiina, Senior Director in charge of Sustainable Development Strategy, Suntory Holdings Limited Group; Representatives from Suntory Pepsico Vietnam Beverage Co., Ltd include Ms. Van Thi Anh Thu, Senior Vice President in charge of human resources; Mr. Le Mac Linh, Deputy General Director in charge of foreign affairs and communications; Representative of Physical Education Department, Ministry of Education and Training: Ms. Pham Thi Thu Ba; Representative of Ben Tre Province attended the closing ceremony with Mr. Tran Ngoc Tam, Deputy Secretary of Ben Tre Provincial Party Committee; Representatives from the Central Committee of Ho Chi Minh Communist Youth Union were Mr. Bui Quang Huy, Secretary of the Executive Committee of the Central Union, Chairman of the Vietnam Students Association; Mr. Nguyen Pham Duy Trang, Member of the Standing Committee of the Central Union, Standing Vice Chairman of the Central Council of the Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization; Representatives of Live &amp; Learn Centre and Tuong Lai Centre; Representatives of sponsors;&nbsp; Representative leaders of departments, ministries, branches and central union; leaders, officers of departments and units of the Central of Youth Union,&nbsp; Central Council of the Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization; Ben Tre provincial leaders; representatives of&nbsp; Young Pioneer Council, Students Association of some provinces and cities implemented the program; representatives of School Board and teachers participated in the program in Ben Tre province, the children who won high prizes in the painting contest \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\", teachers and 500 children of Bao Thuan Primary School attended together.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 382px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/27-12-tk.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">Mr. Takenobu Shiina, Senior Director in charge of Sustainable Development Strategy, Suntory Holdings Limited Group speaks at the closing ceremony</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Speaking at the program, Mr. Takenobu Shiina, Senior Director in charge of Sustainable Development Strategy, Suntory Holdings Limited Group, said: &ldquo;In 2018, the program organized for the first time practical experience activities, forest tours in Ha Giang for 2 primary schools in the area. In addition to traditional activities such as water protection classes for students, training for teachers and volunteers, factory tours for nearly 4,200 students and teachers and volunteers nationwide, installation of 15 on-site drinking water filtration projects, etc. The program also launched E-learning platform, where teachers and people who concerned about environmental protection can access the documents summarized from program implementation process in Japan and Vietnam. Besides, the program also received the active participation of the Ministry of Education and Training in document appraisal work, aiming to replicate the program\'s documents in primary schools nationwide. Looking forward to 2019, we plan to expand the E-learning platform for students and organize Festivals of waste sorting and recycling. We will also continue to work closely with the Ministry of Education and Training to introduce documents of Muzuiku program as reference documents for extra-curricular experience activities in primary schools in Vietnam. &rdquo; Besides that, Mr. Takenobu Shiina also thanked the Vietnamese Central Council of Young Pioneer Organization, the Central of Vietnamese Students Association, local authorities of the provinces participating in the program and the education partners&nbsp; including Live &amp; Learn Centre, Tuong Lai Center for cooperation, coordination and deep support for the program, along with teachers and students who participated and contributed to the success of the program.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 312px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/27-12-tk1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em>Scenes at the closing ceremony</em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">One of the activities in the series of activities within the framework of \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\" program has been positively responded by the children and brought the most meaningful messages was the Children Painting Contest \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\" for children and students across the country. Only after almost 3 months of implementation, the contest attracted more than 500,000 contest entries of children across the country, through their creations, the children showed their spirit, responsibility and consciousness, as well as calling for friends and communities to join hands for protecting water resources. At the ceremony, the contest organizers awarded the prize for the Children Painting Contest \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\".</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 320px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/27-12-tk2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><em>Units received certificates from the program</em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">At the ceremony, the organizers also gave flowers and thanked sponsor units, individual organizations: Ministry of Education and Training, Live &amp; Learn Centre, Tuong Lai Centre and&nbsp; Young Pioneer Council , Students Association of provinces, cities such as Ha Giang, Lang Son, Da Nang, Quang Nam and Ho Chi Minh City have accompanied the program.</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 550px; height: 373px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/27-12-tk3.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em>Delegates looked at the children\'s paintings</em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">In 2019, the program will continue to be implemented in Lang Son, Quang Nam, Dong Nai and Ben Tre provinces. Besides the contents that has been effectively organized for the past 2 years, the 2019 program also has some new and outstanding features including the development and completion of the E-learning platform for students, completion of the education books about clean water for Vietnamese students within the program framework, continuing to coordinate with the Ministry of Education and Training, appraising to introduce the documents of the program \"Mizuiku - I love clean water\" as reference documents for extra-curricular experience activities in primary schools; organizing activities to guide students to classify garbage and protect the environment.</span></span><br /><br />&nbsp;</div>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 9, '0', '2018-12-27 02:25:00', 1, '2019-12-31 03:55:34', 1, NULL, NULL),
(197, 159, 4, 'Opening Ceremony on “Mizuiku – I love clean water” 2019 Lang Son, March 22, 2019', 'opening-ceremony-on-mizuiku-i-love-clean-water-2019-lang-son-march-22-2019', 'news/2019/12/5e0ac72f350f3.jpg', 'On March 22, 2019, Suntory Holdings Ltd. Group (Japan), Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage (Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam) in collaboration with the Ho Chi...', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 456px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/1860.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">The event had the participation of Mr. Nguyen Long Hai - Standing member of Lang Son Provincial Party Committee, Vice Chairman of Lang Son People\'s Committee; Ms. Nguyen Pham Duy Trang - Member of the Standing Committee of the Central Union, Standing Vice Chairman of the Central Council of the Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization; Ms. Tomomi Fukumoto - Executive Officer, Division COO, Corporate Sustainability Division, Suntory Holdings Ltd.; Ms. Wu May San - Senior Vice President and Head of Human Resource &amp; Corporate Communications, Suntory Beverage &amp; Food Asia Pte Ltd; Ms. Van Thi anh Thu &ndash; Senior Vice President-HR, Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage; Ms. Hironobu Kitagawa - Chief Representative, Japan External Trade Organization in Hanoi (JETRO Hanoi), and other senior representatives from the Ministry of Education and Training, Lang Son Province, Suntory Group and Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 400px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/1736.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;<em>Delegates attending the event</em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Mizuiku is an initiative of Suntory Holdings Limited (Suntory) implemented in Japan since 2004. The program celebrates its 15th anniversary in 2019. In 2015, the program was successfully piloted in Vietnam&rsquo;s Northern region with the purposes of educating pupils on water preservation and providing water filtration systems to the remote areas of Vietnam.&nbsp; The original format was customized to suit the Vietnam&rsquo;s conditions and create an interesting learning platform for children. Since 2017, in collaboration with the Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization and the Vietnam National Union collaborated, Suntory Group, Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam have implemented the program at the nationwide scale.</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 419px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/1832.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;<em>Ms. Tomomi Fukumoto was giving a speech at the ceremony</em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Up to the present, the program has been expanded from 6 to 70 schools across Vietnam with nearly 18,000 students receiving education on water resource preservation. 50 clean water filtration systems installed also helped providing clean water for over 23,000 Vietnamese locals. Mizuiku continues to be a part of the Joint Program between the Ministry of Education and Training and the Ho Chi Minh Communist Youth Union for the 2018 &ndash; 2019 academic year.</span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 386px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/919.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em>Delegates and students was sticking their messages of protecting water resources</em></span></span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">2019 marks the 5th year of Mizuiku in Vietnam and is the 3rd year the program be implemented at the nationwide scale. This year the program will be newly established in 17 primary schools in Lang Son, Quang Nam, Dong Nai and Ben Tre provinces, additionally to the current 70 schools. Currently, The Ministry of Education and training of Vietnam is in the progress of examining the Mizuiku materials to allow the materials being used as the reference books for primary students&rsquo; after-class activities. This year the program will also launch the first-time-ever series of picture books for children with the Mizu icon as the teller of water preservation stories.</span></span></span></span><br />&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: 400px;\" src=\"/pic/News/images/1936.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><em>&nbsp;The precious messages conveyed like \"Save water together\", \"Limit the use of nylon bags&rdquo;</em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />&nbsp;</div>', 'news', 1, NULL, 0, 'en', 22, '0', '2019-04-04 09:06:00', 1, '2019-12-31 04:00:35', 1, NULL, NULL);
