span style=\"font-size: 6pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: super; white-space: pre-wrap;\">th</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">) in 2019 and cleaning campaign in order to spread the spirit of protecting the marine environment. The program has the participation of more than 600 officials, youth union members, students, soldiers and people in the city. Besides, on June 30</span><span style=\"font-size: 6pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: super; white-space: pre-wrap;\">th</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">, 2019, a similar activity took place at An Luong embankment, Duy Xuyen district, Quang Nam, with 100 volunteers who are employees of the Da Nang sales office and distributors of Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage Co., Ltd... join together to clean up the garbage.</span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: -12.35pt; text-indent: 12.35pt; text-align: center;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4597a0f4-7fff-4796-e4bc-2892dd3af2b6\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><img style=\"border: none;\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/XogDDEx7nwNCxf034p83xt3xUCuUKXU-rWJPbHbZCiBfha47T_2NIoMQptOp13a0igb15sz2TqBwXe8BqoW1C0oFTM_0eui7ArWiyfPnDBVNBhSdRCMv5K6L2GloIi6p6dSdP0UL\" width=\"602\" height=\"403\" /></span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: -12.35pt; text-indent: 12.35pt; text-align: center;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4597a0f4-7fff-4796-e4bc-2892dd3af2b6\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: italic; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Volunteers agreed to help clean up the coast and embankment</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4597a0f4-7fff-4796-e4bc-2892dd3af2b6\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">In the sweltering sunshine of the weekends, more than 400 Green Summer volunteers, soldiers stationed in the area, officials, youth union members of Hai Phong City, Quang Nam Province, accompanied with 130 Volunteers of Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage Co., Ltd. - distributors, employees in the area, wearing the shirt \"Helping Hands\", with enthusiastic support from REVIVE brand, join hands to clean up garbage at Do Son beach, An Luong embankment&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4597a0f4-7fff-4796-e4bc-2892dd3af2b6\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><img style=\"border: none;\" src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/2liVtsHeUg3VUb1v-XK6xq9HI_eWatFik3y0cX0n8frTNOw65vbTpEX